message: [[WP:AES|←]]Created page with 'I'm a student with a big interest in German literature and metal.  I once owned bunnies.'
/* 'said he had slept in bed with many children' */

took away the ''strange behavior'' out of the lead section - it was not strange on Jacksons part but was made strange by media. he came in his pyjama pants for example because he was rushes from the hospital and had no time to change. media didn't know that and called it strange
changed ''chare his bed'' to ''give his bed'' in the lead section
I brought in the two grand juries that did not indict and added more balance to he Bashir thing
/* 'said he had slept in bed with many children' */ new section
/* Extended-confirmed-protected edit request on 22 June 2019 */ new section
The settlement description was wrong in the backround section too. I also added another quote from ''living with Michael Jackson'' to the incriminating one, in an attempt to make it more balanced.

I changed this sentence because it seemd onesided. In the infamous film scene he did not defend sleeping in the same bed as children. He uses the phrase ''sharing a bed'' but elaborates exactly on what he means by it: he gives his bed to someone else and he would sleep on the floor. Which does not seem half as crazy if you consider that his ''room'' was the size of an appartment. Using a incriminating phrase even though in the same sentence this phrase is explained seems biased.

The previous version catered to a popular believe Jackson ''bought silence''. it is important to note that the evidence for the criminal case back then was examined by two grand juries and found not sufficient to even indict. This should be made clear because the 1993 allegations are used to support following claims. The settlement was for a civil claim of negligence. It did not affect criminal prosecutions.
/* Extended-confirmed-protected edit request on 21 June 2019 */ new section

I deleted the quote about the gut feeling because the source says it was only statet over a decade later in 2017 on a TV show, I did not find this relevant due to the time gap. We should focus on what the jurors said afterwards coming out of the trial. The Times article from 2005 quotes one juror directly, I included that instead.
No reason for lacking neutrality was given apart from ''I feel this was written by Charles Thomson''. I'm not Charles Thomson. The sources are sufficient and neutral as far as I can see.
The Ray Fitzwalter award was missing for his most important piece of work.
/* This page is bias */ new section
